.TH "wil6210_disconnect" 9 "wil6210_disconnect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wil6210_disconnect \- disconnect one connection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" wil6210_disconnect
.BI "(struct wil6210_vif *vif "  ","
.BI "const u8 *bssid "  ","
.BI "u16 reason_code "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vif" 12
virtual interface context
.IP "bssid" 12
peer to disconnect, NULL to disconnect all
.IP "reason_code" 12
Reason code for the Disassociation frame
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Disconnect and release associated resources. Issue WMI
command(s) to trigger MAC disconnect. When command was issued
successfully, call the wil6210_disconnect_complete function
to handle the event synchronously
